\log k - \log (k+1) + \dfrac 1 {k+1}
 \frac1{k+1} - \left( \log(k+1) - \log k\right) = - \left(\int_k^{k+1} \frac{dx}{x} - \frac 1 {k+1} \right). 
0<x<1,\  0<y<1
y=1/(k+1)
y=1/(x+k)
 \begin{align} & \int_k^{k+1} \frac{dx}{x} - \frac 1 {k+1} = \int_0^1 \frac{dx}{x+k} - \frac{1}{1+k} \\[8pt] = & \text{area of that part of the square $0<x<1,\  0<y<1$ that is} \\ & \text{above the line $y=1/(k+1)$ and below the curve $y=1/(x+k)$.} \end{align} 
